data.text:
2017: Brown's starting quarterback, who led the Bears to a win over Bryant with 14-of-27 passing for 152 yards and a touchdown, and 73 rushing yards and two touchdowns...Injured in a start vs. Harvard and was in and out of the lineup for the remainder of the season...Threw for 136 yards and a touchdown vs. Cornell.

2016: Made his debut at quarterback vs. Columbia … completed six of 16 passes for 62 yards.

2015: Gained valuable experience as a member of the Bear’s Junior Varsity team...Athletic Honors: Team Captain in both 2013 and 2014 football seasons, Missouri All State honors, Missouri State runner up 2012, MAPL 2014 first team Quarterback.

Academic Achievements: Graduated from John Burroughs School class of 2014, and Graduated The Lawrenceville School class of 2015, Deans List.
